<HEADLINE>
McCain staff quarantined after letter threat: US Secret Service
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Staff members at Republican White House hopeful John McCain's
Colorado office were quarantined Thursday after receiving a
letter containing a threat and a suspicious white powder, the US
Secret Service said."McCain staffers reported that they had
received an envelope containing white powder in McCain's campaign
office in Centennial, Colorado," said Secret Service spokesman
Eric Zahren.
</P>
<P>
"The staff has been quarantined and the building has been
evacuated."
</P>
</TEXT>
